## Race report

Sunnyhurst Wood presents its own planning challenges with steep sides, fallen trees and increasing vegetation. But it has a good network of paths and at this time of year the undergrowth is not too bad. So l tried to give choices between path or direct. The rain during the week added to the challenge, and possibly to the fun? So l hope everyone enjoyed the courses as much as l enjoyed planning them. And special thanks to Andy and Helen Ellis for taking it on on the day.

Katy Thompson - Planner.

## Map and terrain

**Map notes:**
Map scale is 1:5000, printed on A4.

Green / Red course maps are double sided with map flip.

There are some areas of windblown trees, but courses have been planned to avoid them.

**Terrain notes:**

- 85 acres of mixed woodland with occasional open areas- Steep valley sides and terraces, plus a secondary valley for added complexity- Good path network, runnable forest, and some undergrowth in places

